@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
 Welcome to the first ever Werewolf Software Program to reach AmiNet !!

Werewolf Software has always been a very small group, both geographically and on the point of view of members. We are two students, I, Dave, am 21 and my friend Dragon is 19. I am chief programmer, compositor, graphist of the group. Dragon is chief designer and has (nearly) always the heavy task of creating all sorts of documents for the programs I write. We are situated in Brussels, Belgium, and have been busy with the Amiga for about six years now. We have both a very busy life, and are not able to churn out as many programs as we wanted to. We have also a great many projects under construction at the moment (well in fact since the last couple of years) and never quite seem to find the moment to finish them. However, sometimes, we do find the time to create small utilities, as is the case now:

CDTV ProNet Player is a set of two programs which enable an Amiga connected via ProNet to a CDTV to play any audio CD on it. At the moment the controller is very very simple, but we have found it quite reliable.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
There are two programs in the archives:

 CDTVPlayer , The main controller, a commodity, which needs to be copied
              on the control computer.

 CDPlayer ,   The player, needs to be copied on the boot disk of the CDTV.
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
 The Controller:

 The controller, when run, shows a small window on the Workbench screen.

 Pressing the buttons numbered from 01 through 20 starts the CDTV and plays
 the corresponding track. You can press several tracks one after the other in
 order to play several tracks.

 Pressing 'About' brings an about requester,
 'Iconify' iconifies the program. When iconified, the controller can be brought
 back to life by either pressing the hotkey, double-clicking the AppIcon, or by
 using Exchange.
 Finally, 'Quit' quits the program.

 The program can also be iconified via Exchange.


The Player:
 The Player on the CDTV is not meant to be used manually.



It is important to have the program 'ProNer-run' on the control machine, and to have made the CDTV on the NetWork machine '0'.
@endnode

